[column lg="8" md="8" sm="12" xs="12" ]
<h1>Public Awareness</h1>
<span style="color: #000000;">One of our priorities is informing the public about theÂ  local and global reality of human trafficking. Our web content, printed resources, and custom presentations will open your eyes to the problem, show you the signs of trafficking, and teach you ways to respond.</span>

[/column]
[/row]

&nbsp;

[row]

[column lg=4" md="4" sm="12" xs="12" class="center-block"]

[icon type="glyphicon glyphicon-eye-open" color="#cd2027" fontsize="150" class="center-block"]

[/column]
[column lg="8" md="8" sm="12" xs="12" ]
<h1>Prevention</h1>
<span style="color: #000000;">We prevent trafficking before it happens by educating organizations, ministries, and education systems who have local and/or overseas impact. In turn, these organizations will educate families and communities on how to recognize and prevent victimization proactively.Â </span>

[/column]
[/row]

&nbsp;

[row]

[column lg=4" md="4" sm="12" xs="12" ]
<div style="text-align: center; margin: 0 auto;">[icon type="fa fa-search" color="#cd2027" fontsize="150"Â class="center-block"]</div>
[/column]
[column lg="8" md="8" sm="12" xs="12" ]
<h1>Investigations</h1>
<span style="color: #000000;">We want to see every rescue result in a prosecution, so we alert and cooperate with all relevant law enforcement agencies during every rescue. We also work with the victims to secure their testimonies with the goal of prosecuting all who would buy, sell, or sexually exploit their fellow human beings.</span>

[/column]
[/row]

&nbsp;

[row]

[column lg=4" md="4" sm="12" xs="12" ]

[icon type="glyphicon glyphicon-heart" color="#cd2027" fontsize="150"Â class="center-block"]

[/column]
[column lg="8" md="8" sm="12" xs="12" ]
<h1>Victim Services</h1>
<span style="color: #000000;">We provide 24-hour victim transportation, tip lines, and statewide pickup services. We connect the rescued victims with care provider agencies, law enforcement, and other follow-up services. Our aftercare teams are committed to following up with victims over time to make sure their long-term needs are being met.</span>

[/column]
